post_text:
The Putnam County Public Library is accepting applications for a full-time position. This is a responsible and creative professional position that requires coordinating and directing staff and the day-to-day activities and projects of the Library.

Required: Strong computer skills, experience with general accounting procedures, and office administration experience.

Preferred: Bachelor's degree, prior library experience

Salary commensurate with experience and education. Benefits negotiable.

Pick up an application at the library, or for more information, call Leatha at 660-947-3192. Deadline for applications is Sept. 25, 2020, at 5:00 pm.

post_text: Putnam County Public Library will be closing at 5:00 p.m. on March 19th (today). The Library will remain closed through April 2nd. This date is subject to change, depending on the situation. All the information we have received from the Public Health community suggests that the public well-being is best served by a period of social distancing. The only way we can ensure that in our Library is by closing the facility. The meeting room is also closed to the public. More information will be posted tomorrow (March 20th). Thank you for your understanding and stay well.

post_text:
The movie "UNPLANNED" is now available at the Library for check out. Based on a true story "what she saw changed everything."
All Abby Johnson ever wanted to do was help women. She believed in a woman's right to choose, and as one of the youngest Planned Parenthood clinic directors in the nation, she was involved in upwards of 22,000 abortions.
Watch the movie to see what changed everything for her.

post_text: Bear decided he needed to read the book "The Legend of the Teddy Bear" by Frank Murphy. This is based on a legend from Teddy Roosevelt and a bear. To find out more about the legend of Teddy Bear's come to the Library to read this wonderful book! This would really make Bear happy!

post_text: Bear arrived late today! He is reading "Finding Winnie" The True Story of the World's Most Famous Bear by Lindsay Mattick. He thinks he is really going to like living at the Library! He did tell me that he would like to meet a lot of boys and girls. The most important is he wants them to be kind to him and each other!

post_text: Fun at the Library this morning! They are learning about the Putnam County Public Library. They had a tour of the Library then the Librarian read them a book.
